to hit).<br />Having the levels of monsters affect how you are able to hit them with melee or spells really takes a lot out of the game I think, and makes it a lot more group oriented (which I don't like). Personal accomplishment is hard to find because little can be gotten in this game while it is still useful to us without a group/raid force. <br />What the heck is the deal with making Focus 3 items for spells L44 to L60 only acquirable when we are level 60-65? There should be more opportunities in the game for people to get some decent equipment at their levels by theirselves instead of having to rely on a group.<br />Another problem with the developers is that they nerf one class, and then say "Lets see, Some of these other classes are kind of overbalanced too, so lets nerf them." They never add anything new to the game unless in an expansion, so hardly anything ever gets 'upgraded', things only get downgraded (nerfed) -- Less fun for the players of *all* classes.</span></font></td>
